
[1]chest

   CHEST, n.

   1. A box of wood or other material, in which goods are kept or
   transported. It differs from a trunk in not being covered with skin or
   leather.

   2. The trunk of the body from the neck to the belly; the thorax. Hence,
   broad-chested, narrow-chested, having a broad or narrow chest.

   3. In commerce, a certain quantity; as a chest of sugar; a chest of
   indigo; &c.

   Chest of drawers is a case of movable boxes called drawers.

                CHEST, v.t. To reposit in a chest; to hoard.
